Month of Anti-U.S. Joint Struggle Observed in Britain 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- A joint symposium of the British progressive parties and organizations on the U.S. hostile policy against the DPRK was held in London on June 24 on the occasion of the June 25-July 27 month of anti-U.S. joint struggle.
 Harpal Brar, chairman of the C.C., Communist Party of Great Britain (Marxist-Leninist), made a keynote report at the symposium to be followed by speeches of representatives of different political parties and organizations.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that the U.S. provoked a war of aggression against the DPRK 56 years ago and has persistently resorted to robber-like military threats, sanctions and plots against it up to now. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the U.S. moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK are based on its invariable ambition for aggression to dominate Asia and the rest of the world with the Korean Peninsula as a springboard, they called for intensifying in Britain solidarity activities for supporting the struggle of the Korean people to cope with the ever more malicious tongue-lashing of the U.S. against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was decided at the symposium to coordinate in a concerted way such solidarity activities of political parties and organizations and their anti-U.S. movement by regularly running the coordinating committee of friends of Korea and to organize a celebration rally on the day of the Korean people's victory in the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the symposium were figures and members of the Communist Party of Great Britain (Marxist-Leninist), the Revolutionary Communist Party of Britain (Marxist-Leninist), the New Communist Party of Britain, the British Coordinating Committee of Friends of Korea, the British Friendship Society with Korea and the British Association for the Study of Songun Policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on the invitation were officials of the DPRK embassy in London and a representative of the All-Union Communist Party of Bolsheviks.

Anti-reunification Moves of GNP and Security Forces Denounced in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for the Implementation of the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly issued a statement on June 29 to denounce the "Grand National Party" and the security forces of south Korea for their maneuvers against national reunification.
 It recalled that the security forces in collusion with the GNP recently did not permit overseas Koreans to participate in the grand festival for national reunification held in Kwangju on the occasion of the 6th anniversary of the June 15 joint declaration and kicked up a row in Seoul on June 28 to arrest Yun Ki Jin, chairman of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification who had been wanted for 8 years, by invoking the "Security Law", an evil law of the old times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such acts of the security forces will have given rise to deep concern and resentment of the people, the statement said, adding: The Solidarity for the Implementation of the South-North Joint Declaration will launch a relentless fight to decisively smash all the moves of the GNP and security forces against reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP and the security forces should bear in mind that if they persist in the heedless acts, failing to properly see the trend of the June 15 reunification era, they will face a judgment by history, the statement warned.

Japan's Servility to U.S. Ridiculed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- GI criminals are accorded such "special treatment" in prisons by Japan that they are given chances to have showers everyday, meat is served to them as part of their meals and cakes, coffee and milk are offered to them between meals, according to information released by the Japanese government recently. 
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun Monday observes: This is touching off due resentment among Japanese including families of those who fell victim to the GI crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The criminals should face a due punishment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Such "generous treatment" accorded by Japan to the U.S. criminals there is not regarded as something surprising or strange but as quite a natural and common practice in that country as it is steeped in flattery and subservience to the U.S., its master, to the marrow of its bones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is now offering the U.S. a ridiculous amount of money for the upkeep of its forces every year instead of claiming the payment for the offer of its whole territory as their military bases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whenever a GI crime is reported, Japan just pretends to "punish" the perpetrator, reading Washington's face and underlining the importance of Japan-U.S. alliance. U.S. troops in Japan are not subject to any legal punishment though they commit countless crimes. Even in case a legal action is taken against any perpetrator, it is nothing but nominal to enable him to live in luxury as before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then why is Japan behaving so? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lurking behind this disgusting behavior is a sinister aim. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries frantically seek to hold military supremacy and become a "leader" of Asia with the help of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In a word, GI crimes in Japan are attributable to the shackling U.S.-Japan alliance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the Japanese people are to live in peace free from GI crimes, they should put an end to the above-said alliance and drive the U.S. troops out of Japan to the last man.  This is the best way of rooting out the GI crimes in Japan, the commentary concludes.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Giving Fuller Play to Vitality of Songun Politics 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The Songun politics of the Workers' Party of Korea serves as a treasured sword of justice protecting sovereignty of the nation and peace and security of the country and a powerful engine advancing the era of independence and reunification.
 Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in a signed article. It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reflected in the banner of Songun being held aloft by the DPRK are its firm will and independent mettle to defend sovereignty of the country and the nation and achieve independent reunification at any cost as unanimously desired by the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK are frustrating every move of the U.S. imperialists to block reunification while increasing the defence capability of the country in every way under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years when the U.S. imperialists have become evermore undisguised in their moves to stifle the DPRK and hamper reunification its army and people have protected dignity and security of the nation and facilitated the implementation of the joint declaration, a milestone of independent reunification, with the might of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have made desperate efforts to ignite a war on the Korean Peninsula in a bid to reduce the June 15 joint declaration to a dead document, hamstring the efforts to develop the inter-Korean relations and torpedo the process of reunification but all this proved futile because of the tremendous vitality of the DPRK's Songun politics. It is the spirit and pluck of Songun Korea not to allow anyone to infringe upon the dignity and interests of the Korean nation. No one can encroach upon the interests of the DPRK as long as it is pursuing the Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics is one for defending peace as it is aimed at preventing the danger of war and ensuring peaceful reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has frustrated the moves of the U.S. imperialists to invade it with the ever-victorious Songun politics. Through the "Pueblo," "Panmunjom" and other incidents the army and people of the DPRK clearly showed what awaited the aggressors. No force can match the army and people who have grown stronger a thousand times under the banner of Songun. But for their strength, a new war would have broken out in Korea ten times. It is entirely thanks to the DPRK's Songun politics that peace has been preserved on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will as always work hard to guarantee peace of the country and achieve peaceful reunification, shattering every reckless move of the U.S. imperialists to start a new war with the might of Songun, the article concludes.

U.S. Deployment of New-Type Reconnaissance Plane in S. Korea under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- Commenting on the deployment of "U-2 S Block 20" high-altitude strategic reconnaissance plane in the U.S. air force base in Osan, south Korea, a Rodong Sinmun analyst Monday says:
 This is a grave military provocation and blackmail to the DPRK, being an indication that the U.S. is rapidly pushing ahead in various fields with the extremely dangerous war moves against the DPRK, driving the situation on the Korean Peninsula to the brink of war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As regards the deployment of the plane, the U.S. warmongers claim that it had been planned long ago. But it is nothing but a sophism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nowadays, the U.S. is daily escalating military pressure upon the DPRK with reckless war exercises, massive arms buildup and persistent aerial espionage, while driving the six-way talks for a settlement to the DPRK-U.S. nuclear issue to a rupture by putting up absurd pretexts and fictions. So thick clouds of war are hanging above the Korean Peninsula and a touch-and-go situation is prevailing on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Realities make it crystal clear that the fond talk of the U.S. about "dialogue" and "peace" is a false advertisement to mislead public opinion at home and abroad and its criminal attempt to start a nuclear war on the Korean Peninsula at any cost is entering the stage of practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military strain of the Korean Peninsula carried into extremes by the U.S. imperialists attests to the validity of the option of the DPRK in building up a strong war deterrent under Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Convinced that peace is defended only by arms, the army and people of the DPRK are now in full preparedness to answer a preemptive attack with a relentless annihilating strike and a nuclear war with a mighty nuclear deterrent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists should ponder over the possible consequences of their heedless provocation moves for a war against the DPRK and get out of south Korea promptly with all their military hardware including strategic reconnaissance planes.

Greetings to Meeting of Heads of Government of CARICOM 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- Pak Pong Ju, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, sent a message of greetings to the 27th meeting of heads of government of CARICOM.
 The message noted with pleasure that the meeting was opened amid the great interest and expectation of the people of the Caribbean countries and the international community and extended friendly greetings to the heads of government of different countries and the director general of CARICOM and officials of its Secretariat participating in the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 CARICOM has worked hard to strengthen the integration and unity of the region in conformity with the requirements and desire of its people in the last period, thus registering many successes in the work to achieve sustainable economic development and the common prosperity of the region, the message noted, adding that strengthening the regional integration and unity is an effective way of protecting the sovereignty and common interests from the high-handed and arbitrary practices of the super power and actively coping with the challenge and negative impact of the economic "globalization." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the belief that the friendly ties between the DPRK and the member states of CARICOM would continue to favorably develop in the future, too, the message sincerely hoped that the meeting would successfully discuss all its agenda items and yield good results.

New Kind of Pesticide Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- Great efforts are being directed to preventing possible damage by the harmful insects while weeding in cooperative farms throughout the country.
 Popular among the co-op farms is the pesticide called "clod of agricultural chemicals".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cooperative farms in Pyongyang, South Phyongan and North Hwanghae Provinces are applying the pesticide to protecting various farm crops including rice from harmful insects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The agricultural chemicals are made with various botanical elements, oil substance, emulsifying agent, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The clod, which has a strong contact and permeability, is instantly dissolved in water and forms a thin layer on the surface of water to stick to harmful insects when moving. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It permeates into the body of insect to paralyze the information-conveying system, with the result that insects neither move nor eat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The layer of the agricultural chemicals on the surface of water lasts for two or three days and then forms rings around rice stalks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is very convenient to use. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Walking along ridges between rice-fields, people throw it without using any sprayer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It can be also applied on a windy or rainy day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pesticide affects only harmful insects but does not harm to the human body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Two kilograms are enough per hectare. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pesticide was made by the Mangyongdae Patriotic Compound Microbiological Fertilizer Factory.

Korea Is Proud of Long History of Characters
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The Korean nation has used characters from more than 5,000 years ago.
 During the Kojoson (ancient Korea) period when people in many parts of the world were still in a primitive state, the ancestors of the Korean nation made and used Sinji Characters, the first of its kind in the Korean history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 King Tangun, founder of Kojoson, instructed Sinji, an officer, to create letters. One day Sinji went hunting and saw deer's footprints imprinted on a sandy land. In the footprints, he got a clue for creating letters. The name of the Sinji Characters was derived from the fact. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historical books "Samgukyusa" (historic records of three kingdoms--Koguryo, Paekje and Silla), "Topography of Pyongyang" and "Topography of Nyongbyon" write that the Sinji Characters were used during and after the Tangun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earthenware vessels with Sinji Characters belonging to the period of Kojoson were unearthed in various places including Sinam-ri, Ryongchon County, North Phyongan Province. They prove the fact that the Korean people had used the Sinji Characters from 5,000 years ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Sinji Characters are phonetic and syllabic ones. Their forms differ from those of the ideographic characters of China and of the syllabic characters of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation created Hunminjongum (Korean alphabet) in 1444 by carrying forward the Sinji Characters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hunminjongum is phonetic one that was created on the principle of following the shapes of the vocal organs. It can express almost phonemes. The institution of Hunminjongum enriched the cultural heritage of language of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have consistently developed Hunminjongum into the Korean language with rich and refined vocabularies, expressions and styles.

Struggle against Moves of U.S. and Pro-U.S. Conservatives against Reunification Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front issued a statement in Seoul Monday on the 34th anniversary of the July 4 North-South Joint Statement the core of which is independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity.
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The publication of the joint statement in July 1972 that excited the whole world was a historic event as it brought about a new occasion of improvement in the inter-Korean relations which had remained frozen for several decades and instilled confidence and hope for national reunification into all the fellow countrymen desirous of it. This was a shining result of President Kim Il Sung's Juche-oriented idea and line of national reunification and his indefatigable leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General Secretary Kim Jong Il formulated the three principles of national reunification, the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo put forward by Kim Il Sung as the three charters for national reunification and laid down the five-point policy of great unity of the whole nation. He provided the historic Pyongyang meeting and the June 15 joint declaration with his great patriotic courageous decision, bringing about an epochal phase of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 joint declaration is a declaration of independence, peaceful reunification and great unity of the whole nation, as it is an embodiment of the three principles of national reunification, and a milestone of reunification in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States and the pro-U.S. conservative forces opposed to reunification are making desperate efforts to bar the June 15 era from making evermore dynamic progress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. wire-pulled behind the scene the fascist "Yusin regime" to challenge the historic July 4 North-South Joint Statement even before ink was dry on it. It is still today working hard to bring the June 15 era back to the era of confrontation during the Cold War and leading the situation on this land to an extreme pitch of tension by escalating the moves to isolate the DPRK and ignite a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. conservative forces including the "Grand National Party" are getting frantic in their moves against the DPRK, going against the era of independent reunification in zealous pursuance of the U.S. policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People from all walks of life should turn out as one in the struggle to frustrate the moves of the U.S. and pro-U.S. conservative forces against reunification and preserve and more dynamically advance the June 15 era by the concerted efforts of the Koreans, guided by the idea of "By our nation itself".
